==English==
[[Image:Bowling.jpg|thumb|right|200px|A bowler (bowling)]]

===Etymology2===
From [[bowl]] + [[-er]].

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-əʊlə(r)|-əʊlə(r)]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# {{cattag|bowling}} One who engages in the sport of [[bowling]].
# {{Cricket}} The player currently bowling.
# {{Cricket}} A [[player]] selected mainly for his [[bowling]] [[ability]].
# {{cattag|baseball|slang}} An 1800s baseball term meaning the [[pitcher]].

===Etymology2===
{{wikipediapar|Bowler hat}} <!--Etymology in Wikipedia article-->
From the name of the hatmakers Thomas and William Bowler, associated with early production.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A [[bowler hat]]; a [[round]] [[black]] [[hat]] formerly popular among [[British]] [[businessman|businessmen]].

